summary: This is an email chain between prosecutors and likely law enforcement regarding the status of FBI 302 interview reports and handwritten notes in the Epstein case. It reveals the extensive scale of the investigation, referencing over 120 interviews, and discusses missing documentation.
keyFacts: The document is an email chain dated May 14, 2020, concerning the Epstein case investigation.
It references that collectively, there have been more than 120 interviews conducted in the case.
The correspondence is focused on tracking down missing FBI 302 reports and handwritten interview notes.
The sender is an Assistant U.S. Attorney from the Southern District of New York, indicating prosecutorial oversight of the evidence review.
The email mentions specific interviews (names redacted) where reports or notes are missing, highlighting administrative follow-up in the investigation.
